text: Zebronia mahensis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Thomas Bainbrigge Fletcher in 1910. It is found on the Seychelles, where it has been recorded from Mahé and Silhouette. ==References== *Maes, 2014. "Notes on the Crambidae of Africa with new synonyms and combinations (Lepidoptera Pyraloidea Crambidae)".
